===Etymology 2===
Old English [[gerd|ġerd]].

====Noun====
'''yard''' (''plural'' '''yards''')
# ''(Nautical)'' A long tapered timber hung by its centre to a [[mast]] upon which [[square sail]]s are spread.
# ''(Nautical)'' Any [[spar]] carried aloft.
# (slang) One hundred dollars
# A unit of length equal to three [[feet]] (exactly 0.9144 [[metre]]).

==== Translations ====
*French: (4): yard ''m''
*Italian: (4): [[iarda]] ''f'', yard ''f''

